@kennknowles I addressed your comments, PTAL.

I removed the fault-tolerant support for `Broadcast` - now part of [BEAM-647](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-647) - since it's not as trivial as I first thought.
Also opened: [BEAM-648](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-648) and [BEAM-649](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-649), which came up here as well.

@tgroh I addressed your comments, PTAL.
As for `RunnableOnService`, the SparkRunner was setup with it for a while and the only exclusion is `org.apache.beam.sdk.io.BoundedReadFromUnboundedSourceTest`.
Somehow, it stopped running a while ago, more details here: [BEAM-259](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-259)

